    <p>{`This strategy allows users to continuously create either buy or sell limit orders at a specified price at every time interval. To be more specific, the strategy performs the following:`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`It goes through preliminary checks on every cycle if it can break down the target amount into the number of desired orders and if there is enough balance`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`The `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`target_asset_amount`}</code>{` is the total amount of trades you want the strategy to execute. This target is broken down into smaller orders based on `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`order_step_size`}</code>{` value`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Creates a one-sided limit order (buy or sell) based on `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`trade_side`}</code>{` at the specified `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`order_price`}</code></li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Waits for `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`order_delay_time`}</code>{` value in seconds before creating another limit order (interval between orders)`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Cancels any active order which has been outstanding more than the `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`cancel_order_wait_time`}</code>{` value in seconds`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`You can specify the duration how long the strategy should run by enabling `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`is_time_span_execution`}</code>{`, then set the `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`start_datetime`}</code>{` and `}<code parentName="li" {...{
          "className": "language-text"
        }}>{`end_datetime`}</code>{` parameters`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`If the order step size is bigger than the pending amount or if the pending amount reaches 0, the strategy will stop creating additional orders`}</li>
    </ol>
